Restrictions apply on ammunition orders, please read this entire ad carefully before bidding or offering to buy. title: For Sale/Trade:  TWO Japanese Type 38 Arisaka Rifles, Matching Numbers, Original Bayonet, MUM
postcontent:
These are two beautiful, functional, completely numbers matching Jap Type 38 Arisaka rifles, calibered in 6.5x50 Japanese. Also included is one original bayonet.

My grandfather brought these back from Japan with him after World War Two (WWII). He recently passed away, and nobody in the family is a collector of vintage arms, so we decided to offer them for sale or trade. They are complete, down to the buttplates on the stocks. My grandfather worked as the chief engineer at the Howitzer factory in Wisconsin, manufacturing Howitzers before he went over to Japan. After he got back with these two rifles, he modified one of them to have a shorter barrel, so that it could be more useful to take hunting (which he never did). That is the ONLY modification to either of the rifles. The other one was a longer range/sniper's gun, complete with range-finding iron sights. It was most likely made for a Japanese sniper before the Arisaka Type 97 came out (based off the Arisaka 38 design).

As mentioned, both of these rifles have matching numbers, and the MUM on top is visible and clean, as are the other Japanese markings. Both rifles have been well taken care of - cleaned and oiled regularly, and stored properly. There is NO rust or pitting anywhere on either of these rifles, and the only blemishes on the original stocks were suffered in the hands of Japanese soldiers, during actual battles in Japan.

I have seen these rifles, mostly rusted out, without the proper MUMs, and without any bayonet or documented history sell individually for north of $350. I believe these rifles, in the condition they are in, are worth more than that. I would entertain selling the entire lot for $650 cash. However, I am interested in trading for newer 9mm handguns (manufacturers listed below), or for newer rifles (AR-10, AR-15, Remington 700 or Ruger American Rifle in .308, etc). If you have an offer, I would like to hear it. I may be interested in a trade + cash, on either end, depending on the trade. 

Feel free to email me with any questions you may have.
